# Copy to .env.local and adjust. Vite only exposes vars prefixed with VITE_.

# The app calls OpenF1 directly by default — free historical data (2023+) needs
# no auth. LIVE real-time data requires an OpenF1 sponsor account and MUST be
# reached through the server-side proxy (api/proxy.js on Vercel, or
# server/proxy.mjs locally), which exchanges your credentials for a short-lived
# access token. Never put OpenF1 credentials in the client.

# Point the client at the same-origin proxy instead of OpenF1 directly.
# In production (Vercel) this is set to /api/v1 so requests hit api/proxy.js.
# VITE_OPENF1_BASE_URL=/api/v1
# For the standalone local proxy: VITE_OPENF1_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8787/v1

# ---- Proxy server-side env (api/proxy.js on Vercel; also server/proxy.mjs) ----
# OpenF1 live auth is an OAuth2 password grant, NOT a static key. The proxy POSTs
# these to https://api.openf1.org/token, caches the returned Bearer token, and
# refreshes it (tokens expire after ~1h). Set these as host env vars — never commit.
# OPENF1_USERNAME=your-openf1-username
# OPENF1_PASSWORD=your-openf1-password
#
# Optional tuning:
# OPENF1_TOKEN_URL=https://api.openf1.org/token
# OPENF1_BASE=https://api.openf1.org/v1
# CACHE_TTL_MS=2000
# UPSTREAM_GAP_MS=160
# PORT=8787            # server/proxy.mjs only
